---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import CtaBlock from '../components/CtaBlock.astro';
---

<Base
  title="The Firm"
  description="Revenue Architects created and stewards Revenue Architecture. Built for high-consideration B2B and financial-services firms. Meet the authors."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-content px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
    <p class="eyebrow">The Firm</p>
    <h1 class="mt-4 max-w-prose text-4xl leading-tight md:text-5xl">
      The firm that created Revenue Architecture&reg;.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-prose text-lg text-ink">
      Revenue Architects built and stewards the method. We work with high-consideration
      B2B and financial-services firms — the ones whose buyers take months to decide and
      whose revenue cannot be left to chance.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- The authors -->
  <section class="bg-navy-100/40">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-content px-6 py-section">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl">The authors</h2>
      <div class="mt-8 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
        <article class="rounded-card border border-navy-100 bg-surface p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl">John Stone</h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-teal">
            Founder &amp; CEO
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink">
            John founded Revenue Architects and leads the firm. He is a co-author of the
            method and sets the standard for how engagements are run. [bio to confirm —
            credentials, prior firms, and named results to be finalized by the team.]
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="rounded-card border border-navy-100 bg-surface p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl">Sherwin</h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-teal">
            Co-author
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink">
            Sherwin is co-author of Revenue Architecture and a principal on engagements.
            [bio to confirm — full name, title, credentials, and focus areas to be
            finalized by the team.]
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-prose text-sm text-ink">
        Behind the authors sits a supporting team and a network of Certified Architects.
        They are backing, not a headcount showcase. When you engage us, the authors are
        on the work.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Trademark -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-content px-6 py-section">
    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl">The mark and the canon</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 max-w-prose space-y-4 text-ink">
      <p>
        Others have used the words loosely. We own the mark and the canon behind it.
        Revenue Architecture&reg; is a registered trademark of Revenue Architects, and
        RAOS — the Revenue Architecture Operating System — is the structured body of work
        underneath it: three layers, nine playbooks, twenty-seven plays, five Operating
        Agents.
      </p>
      <p>
        The method is human-orchestrated and AI-operated. That is why a small,
        author-led team can both design an architecture and run it.
      </p>
    </div>
    <a
      href="https://revenuearchitecture.com"
      rel="noopener"
      target="_blank"
      class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-semibold text-teal transition-colors hover:text-teal-600"
    >
      Read the canon at revenuearchitecture.com &rarr;
    </a>
  </section>

  <CtaBlock
    heading="Bring us the problem the architecture has to solve."
    body="We take a small number of engagements. Tell us what you are trying to fix and we will tell you whether it is one for us."
    buttons={[
      { href: '/engage', label: 'Engage the authors', variant: 'orange' },
      { href: '/services', label: 'See the services', variant: 'outline' },
    ]}
  />
</Base>
